2021 Narrative:
-	UNMAS Iraq supported the safe, dignified and voluntary return of displaced people via residential area clearance and providing Explosive Ordnance Risk Education to populations at-risk. Areas of operations included: 
-	Bab Al Saray Market which is the oldest market in Sinjar, built in 1650; 
-	Sinjar Old Hospital;  areas in Bashiqa, Tel Kaif, Sinjar, and Hamdaniya to be used for agricultural and livelihood;  
-	Abu Moriya village in Tal Afar,  an important residential and agricultural area; 
-	and Tel Keif, where an extensive IED belt stretching several kilometres was cleared. The work had crossed over the main Mosul to Duhok road and focused on delivering the required clearance for government contractors to extend and widen this vital arterial link road.
-	UNAMS Iraq conducted 13,259 direct Explosive Ordnance Risk Education sessions in Anbar and Ninewa and Basrah reaching 110,520 beneficiaries and 2,890 cash for work workers and humanitarian workers.
